 [2] ============ SNIP ============
 Marc Landolt 2025-08-19 23:47:38 UTC

Hello MD / RAID Team,

Linux RAID (mdadm) refuses even to read from RAID disks that are attached with forensic hardware write protection (n > 2).

The mdadm switch --readonly does not really help.

The only option is to remove the hardware write protection, but from a forensic perspective, this might not be the best idea.

